reviewText: I thought this film was very interesting.  It presented evidence that I had not heard of before.  Now I too believe that the British govt. killed Diana.
It sounds like a great DVD but haven't been able to watch it yet. It arrived on time,packaged well and safe. Thanks a lot!!!!
Horrible. Don't waste your money. I thought this was a documentary. It's a cheap "talk show"that looks like it was shot by high school kids. Just two men drooning on and on.
Watch with a neutral mind and draw your own conclusions. def gave me a weird messed up feeling, Asks questions that need to be asked.
It sure makes you think.  When Diana died the firm's problem was gone!!!!  Did they or did they not.  Brits version of the JFK mystery.
Interesting but unnerving to watch documentary. This is due to some of the dubious gore details and overall the paranoid tone. Enjoy is you must. Nuff Said!
this is a waste of money.

I don't care whether she destroyed herself or whether an agency of the British Government did it.  She was an international embarrassment and disgraced her position (and I'm a libertarian).  Good riddance to bad rubbish!

This is the first time I've heard of Boston Brakes.  It is a very interesting piece of information as is this whole interview.  Whether right or wrong, we will probably never know because of the amount of evidence that was destroyed or never looked at. I hope to read and hear more about this.
